items.title: Trump says he will send migrants to Guantanamo Bay
items.description: Trump, since taking office last week, has taken numerous actions to crack down on illegal U.S. border crossings and deport undocumented migrants.

items.title: White House says Trump funding freeze remains in effect despite rescinding OMB memo
items.description: The OMB memo had directed federal agencies to pause grants and loans pending a review of compliance with the agenda of President Donald Trump.

items.title: Trump files formal notice of plan to appeal hush money conviction
items.description: President Donald Trump's lawyers formally notified a New York state court of Trump's intent to appeal his criminal conviction.

items.title: Trump classified documents case: DOJ drops appeal against co-defendants
items.description: President Donald Trump had been charged in the case with crimes related to retaining classified documents and obstructing efforts to recover them.
